text.tspan: Number of significant earthquakes, World, 2,150 BCE to 2023
A significant earthquake meets at least one of the following: caused deaths, moderate damage ($1 million or
more), a magnitude 7.5 or greater, Modified Mercalli Intensity (MMI) X or greater, or generated a tsunami. Due to
data availability, recent data will be more complete than older historical estimates.
Data source: National Geophysical Data Center / World Data Service (2024)
